OL,6,FResponding to the points raised by Ms
OL,7,FWest, Parkside Care told ITV Tyne
OL,8,FTees: "Hospital visits in both cases
OL,9,Fwere purely precautionary, as Mr
OL,10,FJohnston was taking blood thinning
OL,11,Fmedication.
OL,13,F"He was swiftly discharged and
OL,14,Freturned to the care home, whose
OL,15,Fresponses to his needs had been swift
OL,16,Fand appropriate.
OL,18,F"Mr Johnston had a nurse call bell but
OL,19,Fdue to his dementia he did not
OL,20,Fconsistently use it. Regular comfort
OL,21,Fchecks were in place.
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G6/12
